04:36.867 --> 04:38.367
-Fifteen.

04:38.400 --> 04:41.333
-Okay, so what exactly happened?
-Haha... we came in,

04:41.367 --> 04:44.833
and you know, we saw
the police presence around,

04:44.867 --> 04:47.833
the helicopter,
and we went in, the dog
was barking,

04:47.867 --> 04:51.167
and we started walking
through the house
into the bedroom,

04:51.200 --> 04:53.767
and my wife's looking,
and she can't fi--
she finds her purse,

04:53.800 --> 04:56.900
can't find her wallet.
And then she's in the closet,

04:56.933 --> 05:00.133
and we're on the bed,
all of a sudden she starts
screaming. She had moved

05:00.167 --> 05:05.167
this one portable-type, uh,
ch-- chest, you know,
a plastic chest of drawers,

05:05.200 --> 05:10.233
and this guy jumped out.
She ran out. David and I
slammed the door

05:10.267 --> 05:13.267
and held him in the closet
in our back bedroom.

05:13.300 --> 05:15.633
-He almost took the purse
and I said, "Can I have
my wallet?"

05:15.667 --> 05:17.833
So...
-Okay, so you left it
in here?

05:17.867 --> 05:21.067
-I left it in the closet
where he was hiding.

05:21.067 --> 05:22.800
-Which purse is it
that he took it out of?

05:22.833 --> 05:25.633
-This purse,
that was in the closet
where he was hiding.

05:25.667 --> 05:27.967
-It was in the closet
where he was hiding.
-Where I was walkin' around.

05:28.067 --> 05:30.233
-You said his stuff
is in the bathroom?
-My-- The stuff-- Some

05:30.267 --> 05:32.833
of the stuff from my purse
was in the bathroom floor.

05:32.867 --> 05:34.467
-Okay.
You picked it all up, though?

05:34.500 --> 05:37.433
-Uh, yeah, basically,
it was just this hair thing,
and it was over there.

05:37.467 --> 05:40.267
And, um, that's when
I knew, and I saw
that my wallet,

05:40.300 --> 05:43.600
my purse
was in the right place
(clears throat).

05:43.633 --> 05:46.667
-I-- I think I broke this.
-That's fine.

05:46.700 --> 05:49.567
-No, I broke that,
'cause I was slammin',
tellin' him I'm gonna--

05:49.600 --> 05:51.767
(chuckles)

05:53.200 --> 05:54.833
-So how did your dog know
that he was over there?

05:54.867 --> 05:57.900
-Well, my dog went
to the original spot
where the responding deputy

05:57.933 --> 06:01.667
saw the suspect.
Uh, we picked up the odor.
We picked up the track.

06:01.700 --> 06:04.733
We jumped some fences, uh,
he went down the street

06:04.767 --> 06:06.467
after jumping multiple fences.
He went to that canal

06:06.500 --> 06:08.100
that's right over here.

06:08.133 --> 06:09.667
He jumped into some bushes

06:09.700 --> 06:11.400
and the helicopter lost him.

06:11.433 --> 06:13.067
I tracked right up
to those bushes, and he just--

06:13.067 --> 06:15.300
he didn't wanna leave the house.
So we kept goin'

06:15.333 --> 06:17.400
around the house, just seein'
if maybe he was in some bushes,

06:17.433 --> 06:19.767
or maybe
hiding somewhere else.

06:19.800 --> 06:21.633
And all of a sudden
we heard somebody screamin',

06:21.667 --> 06:23.600
which was the homeowner.
The homeowner had come home

06:23.633 --> 06:26.200
and found the suspect
in the closet.

06:26.233 --> 06:28.700
-They were probably home
for 10 minutes before and...

06:28.733 --> 06:30.900
like, when we got in,
I guess the two guys
were still in there,

06:30.933 --> 06:33.267
holding him in.
-Yeah. Yeah. Absolutely.

06:33.300 --> 06:35.833
-So...
-So, it-- It all ended well.

06:35.867 --> 06:38.867
-At least he's goin' to jail
for the night.
-Absolutely.

06:38.900 --> 06:40.300
-Can you stand up?
-What?

06:40.333 --> 06:43.067
-You're up? You're not
gonna fall out on me?

06:43.100 --> 06:47.167
-No.
-You all right in there?

06:47.200 --> 06:49.100
-Yeah, my... knees.

06:49.133 --> 06:51.233
-Try putting your legs
on that side of the car.

06:51.267 --> 06:52.900
-I did, that's what I did.

06:52.933 --> 06:55.767
-Okay. All right.
Do you wish to talk to me

06:55.800 --> 06:56.967
about what just happened here?

06:57.067 --> 06:58.767
-No.
-No?

06:58.800 --> 07:00.533
-Okay.

07:00.567 --> 07:02.833
He's gonna be charged
with, um, one occupied burglary

07:02.867 --> 07:05.500
and two other
burglary to a residence.

07:08.300 --> 07:10.933
-I've worked for the Amarillo
Police Department
for three years now.

07:10.967 --> 07:14.633
My dad's been a police officer
here for 32 years,

07:14.667 --> 07:16.833
and my brother's also
a police officer out here.

07:16.867 --> 07:22.633
And I've grown up in Amarillo
also, so, going from watching
my dad be a cop in Amarillo

07:22.667 --> 07:25.567
and growing up,
going to high school here,
and then being a cop

07:25.600 --> 07:31.233
in Amarillo, it's...
I think it's been a pretty
easy transition so far.

07:31.267 --> 07:33.633
-(radio chatter)

07:33.667 --> 07:37.067
-We got a call saying
that there's a suspicious
vehicle parked behind a church

07:37.100 --> 07:40.367
with no plates.
Uh, the caller said
that there's at least

07:40.400 --> 07:44.833
one person in it,
and they're not sure
why they're there,

07:44.867 --> 07:47.067
so we're gonna roll by
there and see if they're
still there, and see

07:47.100 --> 07:48.367
what's goin' on.

07:51.400 --> 07:54.933
433, we'll be at the vehicle.

07:54.967 --> 07:59.067
It's on the, uh, west side
of the church.

07:59.067 --> 08:01.367
It's occupied by one white male.

08:13.333 --> 08:15.200
-Hello.
-Hello.

08:15.233 --> 08:16.667
-What are you doin'
over here?

08:16.700 --> 08:19.233
-Oh, I'm just chargin'
my phone, 'cause they got
a plug-in.

08:19.267 --> 08:21.233
-Chargin' your phone?
-Yeah.

08:21.267 --> 08:24.267
-Okay. Well, is this
your vehicle?

08:24.300 --> 08:26.500
-Yeah.
-Is there another person
in here?

08:26.533 --> 08:29.800
-Oh, my girl.
She's asleep.
-Okay.

08:29.833 --> 08:32.400
All right, well, why don't you
have any plates
on your car, man?

08:32.433 --> 08:36.267
-It's-- I've been tryin'
to get it legal.
-Okay. Hey, why don't you, uh,

08:36.300 --> 08:38.600
why don't you hop out
of the car and come talk
to me?

08:38.633 --> 08:40.833
-Okay.

08:40.867 --> 08:42.433
-Just for now,
until we get this figured out,

08:42.467 --> 08:44.500
I'm gonna sit you
in the back of my car,
I'm gonna talk to her,

08:44.533 --> 08:46.933
and I'm gonna get
this car situation
cleared, okay?

08:46.967 --> 08:49.167
-Oh, I'm tellin' you
right now, it ain't stolen.

08:49.200 --> 08:51.600
-I kn-- I understand,
but I have to make sure, okay?

08:51.633 --> 08:53.233
What's your girlfriend's name?

08:53.267 --> 08:54.733
-Jessica.

08:54.767 --> 08:57.067
-Hey, Jessica?
-(radio chatter)

08:57.067 --> 09:01.467
-Hey, Jessica.
Can you wake up and talk to me
for a minute?

09:04.300 --> 09:05.800
You okay?
-Yes, sir.

09:05.833 --> 09:09.067
-Are you sure?
Can-- Can you step back
here to the back of the car

09:09.100 --> 09:10.600
and talk to me?

09:13.133 --> 09:15.067
You have an ID on you?

09:21.400 --> 09:23.467
Thank you.
Come-- Come on back here.

09:26.067 --> 09:28.333
Is there anything illegal
in the car you're not supposed
to have?

09:28.367 --> 09:31.500
-No, sir.
-What are y-- What are y'all
doin' back here tonight?

09:31.533 --> 09:34.567
-He was just chargin'
his phone and I was
just layin' down.

09:34.600 --> 09:37.167
-Okay. Cool.
What I'm gonna have you do
for a second, is I'm gonna

09:37.200 --> 09:40.133
have you sit on that ledge
right there while I get
this car situation

09:40.167 --> 09:42.067
straightened out,
'cause it doesn't have
any plates on it.

09:42.067 --> 09:44.433
-Okay.
-And I need-- I need
to get you outta here

09:44.467 --> 09:46.067
so I can check it out.
-(object hitting ground)

09:46.067 --> 09:47.367
-Ah, (bleep).

09:47.400 --> 09:50.833
That was all I had. That pipe.
-Well, you got a pipe on you.

09:50.867 --> 09:53.400
I'm gonna ask again--
Is there anything illegal
in the car?

09:53.433 --> 09:56.100
You need to be honest with me.
-Not anymore.

09:56.133 --> 09:58.333
-There's no drugs in the car.
-No, sir.

09:58.367 --> 09:59.667
-Nothin', not even a little bit
of weed?

09:59.700 --> 10:01.100
-No, sir. Go check.
-Whatsoever.

10:01.133 --> 10:03.067
-No.
-Okay. Do you have anything
on you I need to know about,

10:03.100 --> 10:04.833
anything illegal?
-No.

10:04.867 --> 10:06.500
-Okay, do you mind
if I search you real quick?

10:06.533 --> 10:08.867
-No, sir.
-Okay, put your hands
right here for me.

10:08.900 --> 10:10.467
Put your hands right here.

10:14.233 --> 10:17.767
Okay. Uh, go ahead
and have a seat on that ledge
right there. Just sit there

10:17.800 --> 10:19.400
and cross your legs
for a minute, okay?

10:20.700 --> 10:23.100
Is there anything illegal
in the car?

10:23.133 --> 10:26.033
-No, sir.
-'Kay, do you care
if I search the car?

10:26.067 --> 10:28.467
-Actually, yeah.
-You do care
that I search the car?

10:28.500 --> 10:31.533
-Yeah. I got a lotta my own
personal effects in it,
'cause like I said,

10:31.567 --> 10:33.633
I sleep in it.
-I understand.

10:33.667 --> 10:36.433
You understand that when you,
uh, say there's-- you don't
want us to search,

10:36.467 --> 10:38.567
that kinda seems like
there is somethin' illegal
in there, right?

10:38.600 --> 10:40.100
-There ain't nothin'
illegal in it.
-Okay.

10:40.133 --> 10:42.100
I just wanted my stuff
to be left alone, okay?

10:42.133 --> 10:46.667
Y'all pulled in 'cause
y'all expect the car to be
illegal, well, I'm tellin' you

10:46.700 --> 10:51.500
the car's legal, as far as--
I just haven't gotten it
fully done yet.

10:51.533 --> 10:52.567
-Okay.

10:54.900 --> 10:58.733
Hey, Jessica, I'm gonna sit you
in the back of his car
for a minute right now, okay?

10:58.767 --> 11:00.967
Step back here.

11:01.067 --> 11:04.200
Your boyfriend doesn't want me
to search the car, what--
what's-- what's in that car,

11:04.233 --> 11:05.900
Jessica, I want you
to be honest with me.

11:05.933 --> 11:09.267
Honesty is gonna help you
more than anything
right now, okay?

11:09.300 --> 11:11.833
-I have this (indistinct).

11:11.867 --> 11:13.767
-Another pipe.
